                <h2>Nutritional Needs for Rabbits</h2>
                <p>Providing the right diet is crucial for rabbit health and well-being:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Hay:</strong> Fresh hay should be available at all times for proper digestion and dental health.</li>
                    <li><strong>Pellets:</strong> High-quality rabbit pellets provide essential nutrients. Avoid overfeeding to prevent obesity.</li>
                    <li><strong>Vegetables:</strong> Offer fresh vegetables like carrots, lettuce, and bell peppers as part of a balanced diet.</li>
                    <li><strong>Water:</strong> Ensure access to clean, fresh water at all times.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Avoid giving sugary or starchy foods, and consult with a vet for specific dietary recommendations.</p>
